Date:  0/0/1981
Source:  Weeds of Roadsides
Author:  TAYLOR
Vol / Page:  65
Edition:
Quote:  GREATER BINDWEED (<i>Calystegia sepium</i>) Perennial with several stems like climbing beans and twisting the same way ... Trumpet-shaped flowers ... white, or especially in the North Island, light pink ... There are native forms of this species.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1982
Source:  Stewart Island Plants
Author:  WILSON
Vol / Page:  42
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Calystegia tuguriorum</i> NATIVE BINDWEED ... Convolvulus ... High climbing, twining stems with thin leaves. Flowers white, conspicuous. ... [Introduced] CONVOLVULUS or GREAT BINDWEED (*<i>Calystegia silvatica</i>) has much larger, longer leaves, and larger white flowers ...
